modules.description: This module implements monadic operations for handling asynchronous HTTP requests in the context of a Bitcoin client. It provides `return`, `fail`, `bind`, and `catch` functions to compose and sequence effectful computations that may fail, specifically over HTTP interactions. It is used to build reliable, error-resilient request pipelines when communicating with Bitcoin nodes or APIs.

This module implements asynchronous HTTP client operations for interacting with Bitcoin nodes over IPv4 addresses. It provides a `post_string` function to send raw string payloads to a specified URI on a Bitcoin node, including headers, host, port, and IP address configuration. It is used to make low-level, asynchronous HTTP POST requests to Bitcoin RPC endpoints or other HTTP-based Bitcoin services.
